reviews.review: The same problem has existed Throughout this latest series. BAD WRITING!!! It needed convenient gimmicks to Progress the narrative. Full of Forced one-liners. With an unoriginal and meaningless plot. I am not sure which is worse The Last Jedi or Rise of Skywalker. The Star Wars universe has limitless potential but Disney and J. J.  found the only black hole in a galaxy.

I thought this movie was an excellent ending to the Star Wars Skywalker franchise. The story shows a lot of surprises that I personally thought would had never happened. I feel as if there were a few things that happened that were rushed but overall it was a fantastic showing and definitely one of my favorite Star Wars movies made.

Liked that everything was tied up. Disliked that most of the movie was basically black & white, only the jungle scenes had some color. I realize space is black & white, but clothes dont have to be.

Disney LucasFilm had good ideas, talented people, and release dates. Unfortunately, they didn't have a story. IMO this move slipped too far into Michael Bay/ Zack Snyder territory. 

It's clear that there were some early conflicts within LucasFilm and there was a LOT of studio interference at the Disney level, but I hope they understand that audiences want BETTER STAR WARS MOVIES. 

Also, there is no way that the audience score for this movie is 86%.

been watching these movies since the first one and hav seen all of them more than once.this did a great job of wrapping things up which was no easy task.jj abrams did his usual excellent work great everything
it was a great movie to finish up the Star Wars movies, not saying there won't be others, go and enjoy this movie!

Nailed practically all the aspects of what star wars meant to me. 
After two poor movies they redeemed themselves with this one in a way.
I absolutely love all things Star Wars and this movie is a definite must see.  The visuals and acting were stunning.
Overall good wrap up of the series with many cameo appearances by the original cast. Leaves a few unanswered questions but that was inevitable.
